Winding up will reverse the tape recording.

81
00:10:02,780 --> 00:10:05,610
The alarm clock also contains

82
00:10:05,700 --> 00:10:08,610
a microphone. On - out.

83
00:10:10,460 --> 00:10:13,210
If the hands show 12,

84
00:10:13,340 --> 00:10:16,620
I repeat, 12 o'clock,

85
00:10:16,860 --> 00:10:20,220
a small nuclear explosion follows after 15 seconds.

86
00:10:22,260 --> 00:10:24,250
And, what is most important:

87
00:10:24,460 --> 00:10:27,610
It has a built-in Geiger counter.

88
00:10:28,060 --> 00:10:31,020
That microfilm in Pr...

89
00:10:31,140 --> 00:10:34,020
The anonymous town!

90
00:10:34,220 --> 00:10:37,900
In... that town... was made...

91
00:10:39,260 --> 00:10:42,620
slightly radio-active - and a Geiger counter

92
00:10:43,060 --> 00:10:46,210
would be very useful.

93
00:10:47,460 --> 00:10:50,820
Still, allow me to remark... What if it is a trap?

94
00:10:52,140 --> 00:10:55,100
Of course it is a trap!

95
00:10:55,220 --> 00:10:58,180
Our W4C feels in traps at home!

96
00:10:58,300 --> 00:11:00,610
We won't even change the film

97
00:11:00,740 --> 00:11:03,700
in that lift girl's camera.

98
00:11:03,940 --> 00:11:07,490
And, because she's working for all big powers

99
00:11:07,620 --> 00:11:11,410
and several lesser powers - that town will be swarming with secret agents...

100
00:11:13,660 --> 00:11:16,620
And such troubled waters are W4C's favourite hunting ground.

101
00:11:16,740 --> 00:11:19,810
I am sure, dear Cyril Juan,

102
00:11:22,060 --> 00:11:25,180
that the precious salt-cellar will get into the proper hands!

103
00:11:26,060 --> 00:11:29,020
Keep calm... If salt be wasted

104
00:11:29,140 --> 00:11:32,100
what wouldst thou salt with?

105
00:11:32,460 --> 00:11:35,210
What? - That's the Scripture!

106
00:11:35,460 --> 00:11:38,420
It's the police.

107
00:11:43,660 --> 00:11:47,020
He came to ask about a candlestick - dropped from the window.

108
00:11:48,260 --> 00:11:51,410
I nearly forgot: It also shoots!

109
00:11:53,460 --> 00:11:56,420
Sorry, I'm a bit on edge today.

110
00:11:57,460 --> 00:12:00,850
Good thing this is an allied power.

111
00:12:02,140 --> 00:12:04,610
There...

112
00:12:05,740 --> 00:12:08,700
Gentlemen...

113
00:12:10,060 --> 00:12:13,020
Good luck!

114
00:12:20,460 --> 00:12:23,420
What a man!

115
00:12:26,140 --> 00:12:28,610
Juan...

116
00:12:58,540 --> 00:13:00,820
Cyril...

117
00:13:01,060 --> 00:13:04,020
This trap will kill him!

118
00:13:04,140 --> 00:13:07,610
Such a difficult case - could only be assigned to W4C.

119
00:13:08,860 --> 00:13:12,010
And we'll liquidate him at last.

120
00:13:13,260 --> 00:13:16,410
Then we can sell the salt-cellar to all the other agents.

121
00:13:16,540 --> 00:13:18,580
Excellent work, Resident!

122
00:13:18,700 --> 00:13:21,740
This salt-cellar is worth a billion! - Dollars?

123
00:13:21,860 --> 00:13:24,610
Idiot! Crowns!

124
00:13:25,260 --> 00:13:28,220
Your task

125
00:13:28,460 --> 00:13:32,010
won't be too difficult, Idiot... err... Resident.

126
00:13:32,860 --> 00:13:36,010
In another unnamed city

127
00:13:56,900 --> 00:13:59,860
An agency working for another unnamed power

128
00:14:08,060 --> 00:14:11,020
The famous W4C coming to Prague!

129
00:14:11,140 --> 00:14:13,100
Yes, he is.

130
00:14:13,460 --> 00:14:16,820
What does he want here, anyhow?

131
00:14:17,660 --> 00:14:20,780
He has to hand over something to the White Fog agent.

132
00:14:20,860 --> 00:14:22,980
Then why bother me with this?

133
00:14:23,100 --> 00:14:26,410
Shouldn't we know what it all about?

134
00:14:27,260 --> 00:14:30,410
Well, you may be right... Any of our men available?

135
00:14:33,540 --> 00:14:35,500
Not one of them.

136
00:14:35,620 --> 00:14:39,010
What are you talking about? We have... err... Balsanek, Doruzka...

137
00:14:41,060 --> 00:14:44,020
They have their assignments!

138
00:14:45,220 --> 00:14:48,180
Or... this here... Foustka?

139
00:14:49,060 --> 00:14:51,570
Mr. Foustka is our bookkeeper!

140
00:14:51,660 --> 00:14:54,020
Never mind. He'll do, it's easy enough.

141
00:14:57,460 --> 00:15:00,420
Out of order. - Fetch him here!

142
00:15:02,060 --> 00:15:05,420
How did you get in here? Just when I'm doing the taxes!

143
00:15:05,620 --> 00:15:08,610
What's that?

144
00:15:08,740 --> 00:15:11,410
Where's your place? Don't try to talk me over.

145
00:15:11,540 --> 00:15:14,010
Where's your place?

146
00:15:14,260 --> 00:15:17,010
Nothing doing,

147
00:15:17,100 --> 00:15:19,820
you're a naughty doggie - and you'll stand in the corner!

148
00:15:19,940 --> 00:15:22,610
Now, stay there...

149
00:15:22,740 --> 00:15:24,970
Mr. Foustka, the Chief wants you!

150
00:15:25,060 --> 00:15:28,020
I can't. I'm busy! - At once!

151
00:15:28,100 --> 00:15:31,700
It's the assessment, probably. Stay where you are, and behave!

152
00:15:37,460 --> 00:15:40,210
Come in, Foustka!

153
00:15:40,300 --> 00:15:44,010
Excuse me, this clock is slow.

154
00:15:46,060 --> 00:15:49,020
And punctuality being the courtesy of kings...

155
00:15:49,860 --> 00:15:52,010
That can wait, that can wait

156
00:15:52,100 --> 00:15:55,010
Well, Mr. Foustka, I have - we have

157
00:15:55,260 --> 00:15:58,170
an assignment for you - and it's external.

158
00:15:58,460 --> 00:16:01,820
This gentleman will arrive from Paris by air.

159
00:16:02,020 --> 00:16:04,900
We call him...

160
00:16:05,660 --> 00:16:08,410
W4C - W4C

161
00:16:12,060 --> 00:16:14,420
Follow him from the airport and find out what he's doing here.

162
00:16:14,540 --> 00:16:17,210
And that's all, that's all. - All right, I only...

163
00:16:17,380 --> 00:16:20,020
All this without any fuss or scandal. Give me a call if necessary!

164
00:16:20,140 --> 00:16:22,100
I only wanted...

165
00:16:22,220 --> 00:16:25,020
It's nothing difficult. Here, read up these directions...

166
00:16:25,140 --> 00:16:27,100
You don't understand, I...

167
00:16:27,180 --> 00:16:30,010
I give you two days and it's an order! OK

168
00:16:31,140 --> 00:16:33,500
Aren't you an employee of this Agency? - Yes.

169
00:16:33,580 --> 00:16:36,330
You are? Well then! - It's only

170
00:16:36,460 --> 00:16:39,420
that I've been feeling poorly lately and with that stitch in my side -

171
00:16:39,540 --> 00:16:42,610
I need a dietetic treatment... Will that be a problem?

172
00:16:43,140 --> 00:16:46,260
Don't worry, Foustka- you'll be treated all right.

173
00:16:46,860 --> 00:16:50,010
And if all goes well, you'll be made... chief accountant.

174
00:16:51,420 --> 00:16:53,620
Yes...

175
00:16:55,060 --> 00:16:58,020
You are now our... - Agent No 13 B.

176
00:17:03,460 --> 00:17:06,420
Well, we're spies now, Pydie.

177
00:17:09,260 --> 00:17:12,220
Follow him, he says...

178
00:17:13,460 --> 00:17:15,820
But how do we recognize him?

179
00:17:15,940 --> 00:17:18,820
Where's your manners?! Put your paws down!

180
00:17:20,220 --> 00:17:23,210
W4C is landing in a few minutes.

181
00:17:23,860 --> 00:17:27,570
Task No 1: Eliminate W4C.

182
00:17:29,060 --> 00:17:32,260
Task No 2: Sell the salt-cellar for the highest price.

183
00:17:33,060 --> 00:17:36,450
All the Agencies are greatly interested. The place will be swarming with agents

184
00:17:37,180 --> 00:17:40,140
I repeat, it is worth a billion!

185
00:17:40,460 --> 00:17:42,820
Where are you going to hide it? - In a safe, of course.

186
00:17:42,940 --> 00:17:44,900
Idiot!

187
00:17:45,020 --> 00:17:47,610
Every burglar goes straight for the safe.

188
00:17:47,740 --> 00:17:50,100
I know from experience,

189
00:17:50,220 --> 00:17:52,810
that the most conspicuous place is least conspicuous.

190
00:17:52,940 --> 00:17:55,610
Everything ready at the hotel? - Yes.

191
00:17:55,700 --> 00:17:58,090
To your stations!

192
00:18:54,660 --> 00:18:57,620
Attention, attention! The flight from Paris has just landed

193
00:18:58,500 --> 00:19:00,970
The flight from Paris has just landed.

194
00:19:56,460 --> 00:19:58,420
Qu'est-ce que c'est monsieur?

195
00:19:59,340 --> 00:20:02,300
Looking for a light blue car, sir?

196
00:20:05,780 --> 00:20:09,010
My aunt has a light blue one. - Your uncle is expecting you.

197
00:20:19,260 --> 00:20:21,820
Have all passengers alighted yet?

198
00:20:21,940 --> 00:20:24,900
Gone through the customs already. - This one too?

199
00:20:31,660 --> 00:20:33,620
Funny!

200
00:20:33,780 --> 00:20:36,210
Here we are

201
00:20:36,340 --> 00:20:39,010
What does this mean?!

202
00:20:39,220 --> 00:20:42,180
The light blue car is being repaired.

203
00:21:30,580 --> 00:21:33,810
We're getting near, get ready!

204
00:21:36,060 --> 00:21:39,020
Step on it!

205
00:22:04,460 --> 00:22:07,420
Get back there!

206
00:22:14,380 --> 00:22:17,580
Get out and push!

207
00:22:27,700 --> 00:22:30,010
Dear me...

208
00:22:30,140 --> 00:22:33,100
Such a lot of glass -

209
00:22:33,420 --> 00:22:36,410
that's pretty inconsiderate...

210
00:22:36,660 --> 00:22:40,410
Pydie, I got no patches.

211
00:22:42,220 --> 00:22:45,210
Darn it! Get away!

212
00:22:48,460 --> 00:22:51,210
It's empty!

213
00:22:51,380 --> 00:22:54,340
What's up? Where's the fire?

214
00:22:56,980 --> 00:22:59,970
Come here, Pydie!

215
00:23:00,860 --> 00:23:03,420
Hide here, quick!

216
00:23:05,660 --> 00:23:08,410
See him?

217
00:23:12,980 --> 00:23:16,020
That's him all right. After him!

218
00:23:32,540 --> 00:23:35,610
Instead of arriving by plane - he comes up from a sewer!

219
00:23:37,140 --> 00:23:40,100
Or is it a remote heating?

220
00:23:44,460 --> 00:23:47,420
Who's down there? I see you!

221
00:23:49,660 --> 00:23:52,810
You won't come out? Just you wait...

222
00:23:55,260 --> 00:23:58,220
Good Lord, what a stink...

223
00:24:08,460 --> 00:24:11,020
Home already, Pydie?

224
00:24:11,140 --> 00:24:13,810
Good doggie...

225
00:24:13,900 --> 00:24:16,860
Found out anything? Calm down...

226
00:24:17,060 --> 00:24:20,020
What's up? What's the matter with you?

227
00:24:24,180 --> 00:24:27,300
All right, I'm coming! No one's going to steal it!

228
00:24:28,900 --> 00:24:31,860
Now lead on!

229
00:24:32,060 --> 00:24:35,020
Not so fast - I'm no dog!

230
00:24:37,420 --> 00:24:40,380
Which way? Make up your mind!

231
00:24:54,140 --> 00:24:57,420
Where shall we put it? - Into the safe, of course!

232
00:24:59,660 --> 00:25:02,810
Every fool - goes straight for the safe!

233
00:25:02,940 --> 00:25:05,820
I know from experience -

234
00:25:05,940 --> 00:25:09,220
the most conspicuous place to be least conspicuous.

235
00:25:14,180 --> 00:25:17,140
You got to think a bit... Aha

236
00:25:44,140 --> 00:25:46,730
Know him?

237
00:25:46,860 --> 00:25:50,380
No... He's cunningly disguised.

238
00:25:52,620 --> 00:25:55,820
I'll sound him myself!

239
00:26:01,660 --> 00:26:04,620
No, I won't let you in!

240
00:26:04,740 --> 00:26:07,890
Don't wave your arms - calling attention to me!

241
00:26:08,260 --> 00:26:11,010
Just take a look at yourself!

242
00:26:11,140 --> 00:26:14,420
Oh... I'm from the street-cleaning department.

243
00:26:14,660 --> 00:26:17,620
Hmmm... - All right... no street-cleaning.

244
00:26:17,700 --> 00:26:20,820
I'm going to tell you - but don't give me away.

245
00:26:21,460 --> 00:26:24,740
I might get into trouble. I am the agent No 13B.

246
00:26:25,860 --> 00:26:28,010
Are you? Hmmm...

247
00:26:29,060 --> 00:26:32,020
I see... Come on in!

248
00:26:33,820 --> 00:26:36,460
Come on!

249
00:26:36,540 --> 00:26:39,500
Come in, come in! - Shush, be a good boy...

250
00:26:40,060 --> 00:26:43,020
Here's a brush.

251
00:26:43,140 --> 00:26:45,100
Thanks

252
00:26:45,220 --> 00:26:48,210
Towel and soap at the lavatory. OK

253
00:26:54,860 --> 00:26:57,820
A dog!

254
00:27:19,060 --> 00:27:22,020
Is that your dog? - Yes.

255
00:27:22,140 --> 00:27:25,420
I can't let it in. - It's a trained dog.

256
00:27:25,660 --> 00:27:28,730
Well, as it's your...

257
00:27:29,540 --> 00:27:32,740
What's your assignment here, anyway?

258
00:27:32,860 --> 00:27:34,980
I can't tell you. - Why?

259
00:27:35,060 --> 00:27:38,100
Well, it's so secret - that I don't know myself.

260
00:27:38,260 --> 00:27:41,010
A darn difficult job this!

261
00:27:41,140 --> 00:27:44,420
Well, thank you very much. - Don't mention it.

262
00:27:46,460 --> 00:27:48,770
Who is it?

263
00:27:48,980 --> 00:27:51,410
An imbecile!

264
00:27:52,460 --> 00:27:55,980
And that's him? - Yes, disguised too.

265
00:27:57,780 --> 00:28:01,010
A small smile plays on my face

266
00:28:01,780 --> 00:28:05,010
hiding the sadness inside

267
00:28:06,060 --> 00:28:09,420
But when the tears flow from my eyes

268
00:28:10,460 --> 00:28:14,010
life feels sweet

269
00:28:14,300 --> 00:28:17,580
A face of lies and deception

270
00:28:19,060 --> 00:28:22,420
that only a young girl can see

271
00:28:22,860 --> 00:28:26,610
